---------------------------------------------------------------
Version history and copyright information for WBB/WC simulation
---------------------------------------------------------------

Jul 23, 2010 - Joachim Kopp
- Switched to new LBNE fluxes for 120 GeV beam

Feb 3, 2010 - Joachim Kopp
- Beam power is now a variable ("BEAM_POWER")

Feb 2, 2010 - Joachim Kopp
- Fiducial mass of far detector is now a variable ("MASS")
- glb files modularized

Nov 17, 2009 - Joachim Kopp
- Declared all near detector channels as "NOSC" to improve speed

Nov 13, 2009 - Joachim Kopp
- Switched to new flux file
- Adjusted luminosity to 2.3 MW for 120 GeV beam
  (for 3 years (3 x 2e7 s), this corresponds to 72e20 pot)
- Adjusted luminosity to 2.0 MW for 60 GeV beam
  (for 3 years (3 x 2e7 s), this corresponds to 125e20 pot)
- Implemented near/far systematics

Mar 5, 2008 - Patrick Huber
- adjusted to nuflux

Feb 2007 - Mark Dierckxsens
- New smearing functions from Milind
  Assume they are the same for neutrinos and anti-neutrinos
- Fine tweaking of efficiencies, changing baseline.
- Error on background is 5%

Jan 2007 - Mary Bishai
- New normalizations, efficiencies for WCC from Chiaki Yanagisawa

Jul 12, 2006
-  matrices for energy resolution extended.  The new
   ones are used here.

Jun 16, 2006 - Christine Lewis
- flux file changed

Apr 22, 2006 - Christine Lewis
- Baseline changed from 2540 (BNL->HS) to 1300km (FNAL->HS)

May 26, 2005 - Patrick Huber
- Original glb file


---------------------------------------------------------------
Note on the normalization factors
---------------------------------------------------------------

NOTE: Conversion from pot to time according to LBNE baseline design for CDR:
   FNAL beam 7.3 x 10^20 POT per year (708kW, 1.98e7s per yr, 120GeV)
(information from Lisa Whitehead, 13 Aug 2010)

At 120 GeV: 2.3 MW are equivalent to
  2.3e6 J/s / (1.6e-19 eV/J) / (120e9 eV/pot) * 1.98e7 s/yr * 3 yr
    = 71e20 pot

Event rate [Neutrinos/GeV] =
   flux @ 1300 km [Neutrinos/GeV/pot/m^2] * 1300^2
 * 10^-38 * 10^-4 m^2/cm^2 * cross section [10^-38 cm^2]
 * Number of pot
 * 6.02e32 nucleons/kt * Detector mass [kt]

==> @norm = 1300^2  *  10^-38*10^-4  *  10^20  *  6.02e32
          = 1300^2  *  6.02 * 10^10
          = 1.017e17

The normalization factor from the LBNE file is
  5.19*7.504*10^12*1300*1300/120.0 / 5.202 = 1.054e17



